    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add missing log statement for PNF stop request error handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `pnf_handle_pnf_stop_request` function in the PNF module was missing a log statement when the PNF was not in the correct state to handle a stop request. This made debugging difficult when the function would silently fail to process stop requests.\n\nThe issue was identified when investigating why PNF stop requests were not being handled properly in certain scenarios. Other similar functions in the same file were properly logging error conditions, but this function was missing the log statement in its error handling path.\n\nThe fix adds a log statement that matches the pattern used in other functions in the same file, providing consistent error logging across all PNF request handlers.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/pnf/src/pnf.c`: Added missing `NFAPI_TRACE` log statement in `pnf_handle_pnf_stop_request` function when PNF is not in RUNNING state.\n\n"
}